Well  it's  been a while since I last sat down at the computer to  tell  the
Amiga  community of my developments and I apologise.  The only reason behind
that is that it's been so bloody hectic round my neck of the woods the  last
few months that I don't even know where to start.

First  of all,  anyone who want's a mad weekend of Old Skool,  Drum &  Bass,
Jungle and Hard House should come up to Birmingham from the 15th to 18th  of
June.   On  the 15th me @1(XLR8)@5  and James@1 (Mixmad)@5  will be playing  in  the
basement  bar of The Gallery on Smallbrook Queensway in the City Centre.   I
played  there a few weeks back and it was absolutely storming with  MC  Jaff
and  DJ  Infamous tearing the place down after I stepped off of  my  2  hour
set. So now you know!

On the 16th it's Music First at the Venue,  Branston Street,  Hockley.  Kool
FMs finest DJs rip it up with MCs Accapello and Biggy alongside some of  the
worlds best Drum and Bass DJs. Tickets for that will be@3 £10@5.

On the 17th it's the mighty@4 FLASHBACK@5 at The Que Club!!!!  Yes that's right,
over  9 hours of underground musical mayhem is to be unleashed on the cities
finest club with an excellent line up@1:
