You  want  more?!  This event will be spread over 3 main arenas  with  other
bars and rooms to explore,  Mixmag will be there along with Core Productions
with  their film crew and there's also a pre-club party at The Gallery  with
Glenn  Aston back to back with Nexus. #8 PHEWY!@1  For more info phone 0121  472
0777 or goto www.flashback96.com
@5
What  else has been happening.  I finally sold my old Escort,  read My First
Car article and I´m involved with a project called The Blue Zone.  This is a
new  play / project type thing which is being held at the Birmingham MAC  at
Cannon Hill Park in Edgbaston.  It's about a group of young people and their
lives and going to clubs,  pubs,  taking drugs etc etc.  Where I come in  is
they  need a DJ to do some live scratching and mixing over one of the  zones
@1(the  project is split into 4 separate zones)@5.  It's all very  exciting  and
when I get some firm dates I´ll let you know.

I'm  DJing  in  France on Saturday the 5th of August.  I  have  yet  to  get
location and all the rest of it but I´m told it's some mad outdoor thing  in
a field with a barn.@2 My sort of rave!!!!#8 :-)
@5
Bought some new CDs@1 -@3 Aphex Twin,  Windowlicker. Eminem, My Name Is. Eminem,
Guilty Consscience.@5  I know they are old but it had to be done,  they're all
great tunes.




I  have finally got some new decks.  I bought two Technics SL120mk2s  and  a
Vestax PMC-03A from Orange DJ Megastore Mail Order.  The whole DJ setup with
carts,  headphones etc cost a whopping £810 but believe me,  it's worth  it.
If  you  haven´t got Technics yet then get your pennies saved 'cos when  you
do  get them you'll never get rid of them.  The mixers pretty good too  with
strong  faders and a good design.  If you can get that package  any  cheaper
than i did then write in, we are always after the cheapest bargains.

Don't forget,  I´ve got 340 Dance, House, Trance, Hip Hop, Soul records here
so if your looking to expand your collection you know who to call.
